---
// FeaturesSection — bento grid of 5 feature cards
---

<section class="features">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-label reveal">Core Strengths</p>
    <h2 class="section-title reveal">The contract layer between intent,<br/>code, and delivery.</h2>

    <div class="bento">
      <div class="bento-card bento-graph reveal" style="--reveal-delay: 0s">
        <div class="bento-label">Verifiable Graph</div>
        <h3>One graph for requirements, designs, tasks, and evidence.</h3>
        <p>Every document becomes a typed node with computed reverse links. Query any slice with <code>supersigil context</code>, inspect coverage, and export the structure as Mermaid or Graphviz DOT.</p>
        <div class="bento-visual graph-mini" aria-hidden="true">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 240 120">
            <g stroke="#c9a55c" stroke-width="0.6" opacity="0.3">
              <line x1="120" y1="30" x2="60" y2="60"/>
              <line x1="120" y1="30" x2="180" y2="60"/>
              <line x1="60" y1="60" x2="40" y2="95"/>
              <line x1="60" y1="60" x2="90" y2="95"/>
              <line x1="180" y1="60" x2="160" y2="95"/>
              <line x1="180" y1="60" x2="210" y2="95"/>
            </g>
            <circle cx="120" cy="30" r="4" fill="#c9a55c" opacity="0.8"/>
            <circle cx="60" cy="60" r="3" fill="#5a8f9f" opacity="0.7"/>
            <circle cx="180" cy="60" r="3" fill="#5a8f9f" opacity="0.7"/>
            <circle cx="40" cy="95" r="2.5" fill="#555" opacity="0.5"/>
            <circle cx="90" cy="95" r="2.5" fill="#555" opacity="0.5"/>
            <circle cx="160" cy="95" r="2.5" fill="#555" opacity="0.5"/>
            <circle cx="210" cy="95" r="2.5" fill="#555" opacity="0.5"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bento-card bento-ai reveal" style="--reveal-delay: 0.08s">
        <div class="bento-label">Agent-Ready Context</div>
        <h3>Structured scope for coding agents.</h3>
        <p>Core commands emit <code>--format json</code>. Agents can load one document, inspect linked criteria, plan missing work, and re-verify against the same contract.</p>
        <div class="bento-snippet" aria-hidden="true">
          <code><span class="c-muted">$</span> supersigil context auth/req --format json</code>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bento-card bento-verify reveal" style="--reveal-delay: 0.16s">
        <div class="bento-label">CI Guardrails</div>
        <h3>Catch broken refs, missing evidence, and stale specs before release.</h3>
        <p><code>supersigil verify</code> checks the graph, while tracked files flag specs that need review after code changes. Draft gating keeps iteration light until you are ready to enforce.</p>
        <div class="bento-snippet" aria-hidden="true">
          <code><span class="c-red"><b>&#10006;</b></span> <span class="c-muted">[missing_verification_evidence]</span> Criterion "valid-creds": no matching evidence</code>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bento-card bento-examples reveal" style="--reveal-delay: 0.12s">
        <div class="bento-label">Executable Examples</div>
        <h3>Use runnable docs when a static snippet is not enough.</h3>
        <p>Embed shell, HTTP, Rust, or custom-runner examples directly in spec docs. Passing examples can count as evidence inside the same verification pass.</p>
        <div class="bento-snippet" aria-hidden="true">
          <code><span class="c-gold">&lt;Example</span> <span class="c-teal">runner</span>=<span class="c-str">"http"</span> <span class="c-teal">verifies</span>=<span class="c-str">"…#due-date"</span><span class="c-gold">&gt;</span></code>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bento-card bento-rust reveal" style="--reveal-delay: 0.2s">
        <div class="bento-label">Pluggable Evidence</div>
        <h3>Start simple, then add richer discovery where your stack supports it.</h3>
        <p>Use tags or file globs by default. Add ecosystem integrations such as Rust <code>#[verifies(...)]</code> discovery when you want test evidence to flow into the graph automatically.</p>
        <div class="bento-snippet" aria-hidden="true">
          <code><span class="c-muted">// supersigil:</span> <span class="c-teal">auth:valid-creds</span></code>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .features {
    padding: 8rem 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
  }
  .bento {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    grid-template-rows: auto auto;
    gap: 1.25rem;
    margin-top: 3rem;
    grid-template-areas:
      "graph ai     verify"
      "graph examples rust";
  }
  .bento-graph    { grid-area: graph; }
  .bento-ai       { grid-area: ai; }
  .bento-verify   { grid-area: verify; }
  .bento-examples { grid-area: examples; }
  .bento-rust     { grid-area: rust; }

  .bento-card {
    padding: 2rem;
    background: var(--bg-card);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 12px;
    transition: border-color 0.3s, background 0.3s;
    position: relative;
    overflow: hidden;
  }
  .bento-card:hover {
    border-color: var(--border-hover);
    background: var(--bg-card-hover);
  }
  .bento-label {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.68rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--gold);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }
  .bento-card h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-weight: 500;
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    line-height: 1.35;
    margin-bottom: 0.6rem;
  }
  .bento-card p {
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-size: 0.88rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }
  .bento-snippet {
    margin-top: 1rem;
    padding: 0.6rem 0.8rem;
    background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.25);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 6px;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.76rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    overflow-x: auto;
    white-space: nowrap;
  }
  .bento-snippet .c-muted { color: var(--text-dim); }
  .bento-snippet .c-gold { color: var(--gold); }
  .bento-snippet .c-teal { color: #5a8f9f; }
  .bento-snippet .c-str { color: #a8c97a; }
  .bento-snippet .c-red { color: #d45b5b; }
  :global([data-theme='light']) .bento-snippet {
    background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.04);
  }
  .bento-visual {
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
  }
  .graph-mini svg {
    width: 100%;
    max-width: 240px;
    opacity: 0.7;
  }

  /* Light theme overrides */
  :global([data-theme='light']) .graph-mini line[stroke="#c9a55c"] { stroke: #8a6c2f; }
  :global([data-theme='light']) .graph-mini circle[fill="#c9a55c"] { fill: #8a6c2f; }
  :global([data-theme='light']) .graph-mini circle[fill="#5a8f9f"] { fill: #3d7080; }
  :global([data-theme='light']) .graph-mini circle[fill="#555"] { fill: #9a9590; }
</style>
